This paper is likely to belong to the category of computer science (cs) sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with providing censorship-resistant communication mechanisms. It may also belong to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it utilizes the Bitcoin network for communication. Additionally, it may belong to the sub-categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as it proposes adaptive and cost-effective data communication solutions. Finally, it may also belong to the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it deals with providing secure communication mechanisms.
